<p>This is based entirely on a <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6052784/#CIT0021">study:</a> "Sense of Purpose Moderates the Assocations between Daily Stressors and Daily Well-being". For each data point, I </p>

<p>The dance moves are then encoded using <a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/fpsyg.2019.01389/full">Laban Movmement Analysis</a> techniques to portray emotions.</p>


<p>I was also inspired by an Australian influencer, <a href="https://www.instagram.com/shani.chantel/?hl=en">Shani Chantel</a>, who is all about female empowerment and ending body shaming. She began a small movement called <strong>Free Your Shit Fridays</strong> that urges women to let themselves dance to their favourite music in their underwear, with their kids on their hips and feel the freedom that comes with dancing.</p>

<p>Dance and mental health are also closely linked.<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6657024/">A 2019 study</a> showed that dancing can improve the mental health of persons with chronic diseases - singing can too!</p>

<p>If you are ever feeling a bit down, throw on your favourite tune, belt out that ballad and swing your hips around the house!</p>